Adjust rack to middle position and preheat oven to 400 degrees. Wash and dry all produce.

Pat @chicken breast strips{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; place in 1 #oven-ready aluminum tray{1} (divide between 2 #trays{} for 4 servings).

In a #large bowl{}, combine @coconut milk{5.07%ounce}, @curry powder{1%tablespoon}, @sweet Thai chili sauce{1%ounce}, @chicken stock concentrate{1}, @sugar{1/2%teaspoon} (1 tsp for 4), and a big pinch of @salt{}. Pour over chicken and stir until evenly coated.

Open rice packet; add @microwaveable jasmine rice{1%unit} to remaining #aluminum tray{1} (divide between remaining 2 trays for 4 servings). Break up grains and spread into an even layer, then top with half the @shredded carrots{4%ounce} (all for 4). Sprinkle with @water{2%tablespoons} and top with @butter{1%tablespoon} (for 4, use 2 TBSP water and 1 TBSP butter per tray). Cover with @foil{}. TIP: Place trays on a #baking sheet{} to make them easier to handle.

Place trays on middle rack; bake until chicken is cooked through and carrots are tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Meanwhile, quarter @lime{1}. Pick @cilantro{1/4%ounce} leaves from stems; roughly tear leaves.

Stir a squeeze of lime juice into chili coconut curry chicken.

> The sauce may have separated a bit; simply stir and it will come back together.

Stir carrots and rice together; season generously with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Divide carrot-speckled rice between shallow #bowls{} and top with chili coconut curry chicken. Garnish with torn cilantro. Serve with remaining lime wedges on the side.